## Example 4 — Volume of Hemisphere

Find the volume of a hemisphere with radius 7 ft.

### Step 1: Write the Formula

$$V_{\text{hemi}} = \frac{2}{3}\pi r^3$$

### Step 2: Substitute

$$V = \frac{2}{3}\pi(7)^3 = \frac{2}{3}\pi(343) = \frac{686}{3}\pi$$

### Step 3: Compute the Approximate Value

$$\frac{686}{3}\pi \approx 718.38 \text{ ft}^3$$

### Step 4: Verify with Full Sphere

$$V_{\text{sphere}} = \frac{4}{3}\pi(343) = \frac{1372}{3}\pi$$

$$\frac{1}{2} \times \frac{1372}{3}\pi = \frac{686}{3}\pi \checkmark$$

✅ Answer: The volume is $\frac{686}{3}\pi \approx$ **718.38 ft³**.

